"You bet I would, sunshine."

12:44.285 --> 12:46.548
I can't give up, Carl. That
little girl needs her daddy.

12:46.635 --> 12:49.507
And her Uncle Carl, too.

12:49.594 --> 12:51.422
Remind me to call my daughter
when I get home

12:51.509 --> 12:53.685
and tell her
how much I love her? Eah?

12:53.773 --> 12:57.124
And to meet me
at the police station...

12:57.211 --> 12:59.691
..with $200 bail money

12:59.779 --> 13:01.650
and a pair of pants.

13:02.782 --> 13:05.088
[instrumental music]

13:06.394 --> 13:07.917
This is a good
look for you.

13:08.004 --> 13:11.225
You might want to stick with
this even after the recital.

13:11.312 --> 13:13.923
Victoria, this is a barnyard,
not a brothel.

13:14.010 --> 13:16.404
- Cows don't wear lipstick.
- They don't tap-dance either.

13:16.491 --> 13:18.580
Let's not start
poking holes in reality.

13:18.667 --> 13:21.278
Alright, scoot. Go wipe that off
and put on your cowbell.

13:21.365 --> 13:22.540
And no more
glitter lipstick.

13:22.627 --> 13:25.239
Oh! She stresses me out.

13:25.326 --> 13:28.720
You don't smoke, do you?

13:28.808 --> 13:29.765
How are we doing?

13:29.852 --> 13:32.115
Oh, I think we're gonna be okay.

13:32.202 --> 13:35.118
Our banty rooster came down
with chicken pox, ironically

13:35.205 --> 13:38.078
but think the show
must go on, huh?

13:38.165 --> 13:39.470
I just want to say,
you've done

13:39.557 --> 13:40.820
a remarkable job
with this whole thing.

13:40.907 --> 13:42.952
Oh, well, you've been my rock.

13:43.039 --> 13:45.172
I mean,
if you weren't here, I think

13:45.259 --> 13:47.522
a couple of chickens would be
sleeping with the fishes.

13:47.609 --> 13:51.961
Miss Flynn, I think one
of the pigs pooped his pants.

13:52.048 --> 13:55.617
Perfect. Told you all to eat
light on show night!

13:59.447 --> 14:00.796
It's a big show tonight, huh?

14:00.883 --> 14:02.537
My brother's a donkey.

14:02.624 --> 14:04.495
So is my best friend.

14:04.582 --> 14:06.149
Sophie's my best friend.

14:06.236 --> 14:08.456
Oh, hi, Sophie.
Nice to meet you.

14:08.543 --> 14:10.850
- She's shy.
- Well, she just met me.

14:10.937 --> 14:12.286
She'll warm up to me.

14:12.373 --> 14:14.679
Can you hold my doll
so she can see?

14:14.766 --> 14:16.986
Absolutely.

14:17.073 --> 14:19.423
Is that better, Sophie?

14:19.510 --> 14:20.860
Well, thanks.

14:20.947 --> 14:22.644
I knew you'd
warm up to me.

14:24.776 --> 14:25.908
How's it going back there?

14:25.995 --> 14:27.344
I had to flirt
with one of the janitors

14:27.431 --> 14:30.478
so he'd give me
a drink of his moonshine.

14:30.565 --> 14:31.827
- Opening night jitters?
- No.

14:31.914 --> 14:33.524
Molly's driving
everybody crazy.

14:33.611 --> 14:36.658
I know she's your wife, but
she can be a real B-I-T-C-H.

14:36.745 --> 14:39.182
Hey, that's a bad word!

14:39.269 --> 14:40.967
Wow, you spell good.

14:41.054 --> 14:42.882
Give me my doll back.

14:45.580 --> 14:47.799
Real nice, potty mouth.

14:49.497 --> 14:51.412
Okay, it's a packed house.

14:51.499 --> 14:53.240
We're looking
at a packed house!

14:53.327 --> 14:56.286
Alright, we've worked
really hard to get here

14:56.373 --> 14:58.419
and it's been
a lot of hard nights

14:58.506 --> 15:00.247
and a few tears and some poop.

15:00.334 --> 15:01.813
But I know that

15:01.901 --> 15:04.555
as soon as your moms
and your dads see how hard

15:04.642 --> 15:05.774
you have worked,
that they're gonna be

15:05.861 --> 15:08.168
just as proud of you as I am.

15:08.255 --> 15:09.691
Okay, so go out there and shine.

15:09.778 --> 15:12.346
Shine like the little
stars I know you are.

15:13.434 --> 15:15.740
Go, go, go

15:15.827 --> 15:18.352
Oh, God, I'm glad
we're not charging admission.

15:20.963 --> 15:25.228
- Have a great opening night.
- Oh, that is so sweet.

15:25.315 --> 15:26.751
I really appreciate
all your help.

15:26.838 --> 15:28.188
Oh, it's been my pleasure.

15:28.275 --> 15:29.232
I've, uh, I've enjoyed

15:29.319 --> 15:30.277
the time we've spent together.

15:30.364 --> 15:32.844
It's been
really fun, huh?

15:32.932 --> 15:34.585
Oh! What are you doing?

15:34.672 --> 15:36.936
- I'm married.
- Sounded a little rocky.

15:37.023 --> 15:38.328
Oh, so you thought
you'd just step in

15:38.415 --> 15:40.069
and take advantage
of a vulnerable woman?

15:40.156 --> 15:41.375
No, no, that's not..

15:41.462 --> 15:42.898
Listen, pal, I love my husband.

15:42.985 --> 15:46.771
I mean, I'm flattered,
but what a dink move.

15:48.121 --> 15:49.774
I...I'm sorry
if I overstepped.

15:49.861 --> 15:52.429
Well, overstep your
ass to the piano

15:52.516 --> 15:55.867
and start tickling the ivories
before I start tickling yours!

15:57.391 --> 15:59.697
Damn musicians.

16:02.831 --> 16:05.181
Show business. Sickening.

16:09.707 --> 16:11.535
Trevor!

16:15.322 --> 16:19.326
♪ The other night dear
as I lay sleeping ♪

16:19.413 --> 16:23.504
♪ I dreamed
I held you in my arms ♪

16:23.591 --> 16:27.769
♪ When I awoke dear
I was mistaken ♪

16:27.856 --> 16:30.990
♪ And I held my head and cried ♪

16:31.077 --> 16:33.862
♪ Wah Wah
you are my sunshine ♪

16:33.949 --> 16:36.038
♪ My only sunshine ♪

16:36.125 --> 16:37.909
♪ You make me happy ♪

16:37.997 --> 16:40.042
♪ When skies are gray ♪♪ Gray gray gray ♪

16:40.129 --> 16:44.394
♪ You'll never know dear
how much I love you ♪

16:44.481 --> 16:49.182
♪ Please don't
take my sunshine away. ♪

16:50.661 --> 16:52.924
Trevor!

16:54.839 --> 16:57.233
[applauds]

17:00.932 --> 17:03.674
You guys were amazing.

17:03.761 --> 17:05.720
I'm so proud of all of you.

17:05.807 --> 17:06.938
You really nailed it.

17:07.026 --> 17:09.115
Wow! I don't know what to say.

17:09.202 --> 17:11.639
It was not nearly as horrible
as I thought it was gonna be!

17:11.726 --> 17:13.510
- Oh, really?
- Yeah.

17:13.597 --> 17:14.990
I only started
to doze off once.

17:15.077 --> 17:18.298
But then the silo fell over,
you had me to the end.

17:18.385 --> 17:21.040
Can I, uh, buy you
a little celebratory drink?

17:21.127 --> 17:24.869
No, but, uh, how about
we open a bottle of champagne

17:24.956 --> 17:26.393
and see where
the night takes us?

17:26.480 --> 17:28.134
But you're not
ovulating anymore.

17:28.221 --> 17:30.701
Well, I'm still married to the
man that gives me butterflies

17:30.788 --> 17:33.008
every time I see him
walk into the room.

17:36.098 --> 17:37.491
I just want to say again how..

17:37.578 --> 17:40.537
Yeah, tell your story
walking, piano man.

17:46.978 --> 17:48.110
It's 8:05.

17:48.197 --> 17:49.459
Relax, will you?
He'll be here.

17:49.546 --> 17:51.070
He was supposed
to be here at 7:30.

17:51.157 --> 17:53.246
He's a hillbilly,
they tell time by the position

17:53.333 --> 17:55.422
of the sun or which way
the cows are facing.

17:55.509 --> 17:57.641
They don't know our modern ways.

17:57.728 --> 17:59.861
I'm starting to have second
thoughts about this, Vince.

17:59.948 --> 18:02.255
Hey, we're not hurting
these animals.

18:02.342 --> 18:04.648
We're feeding them
and letting them screw.

18:04.735 --> 18:08.957
Tell me, if you were an ostrich,
you wouldn't want that gig?

18:09.044 --> 18:11.612
This is a lot of money to be
betting on a bunch of birds.

18:11.699 --> 18:13.353
There's no betting involved.

18:13.440 --> 18:15.616
You're building
a secure financial foundation

18:15.703 --> 18:17.835
